   {:e #blake3 "a8e8684416b96b1da811b031ea65286101a784929a8748b2b170f14fb5f7d76a" :a :task/description :v "BACKGROUND: The onboarding cliff kills every methodology tool. Nobody reads manuals. Nobody configures YAML. But everyone can answer questions about their domain. The LLM-bootstrapped init compiles natural language into the formal policy manifest. The conversation IS the first harvest — observations crystallized into structural datoms in the same transaction (COTX pattern). This closes the self-bootstrap loop: the observer defines the rules of its own knowledge game.. APPROACH: (1) braid init without --manifest enters interactive mode. (2) Structured prompts via guidance system: \"What domain is this project in?\", \"What are the things that must be true? (requirements, invariants, hypotheses)\", \"What counts as evidence? (tests, audits, experiments, reviews)\", \"What pairs should be aligned? (spec-impl, requirement-control, hypothesis-experiment)\", \"What would alarm you if it drifted?\". (3) Parse responses into PolicyManifest struct. (4) Generate policy datoms from manifest. (5) Transact as genesis alongside bootstrap datoms. (6) Record the conversation as :exploration/* observation datoms in the SAME transaction. (7) Show the generated manifest for user review before committing. (8) Uncertainty markers: if user says \"I think\" or \"maybe\", set confidence < 1.0 on the policy datom. (9) braid init --manifest ddis.edn loads pre-built manifest (backward compat). (10) braid init --manifest - reads manifest from stdin (for programmatic use).. ACCEPTANCE: (A) Interactive init produces valid policy manifest. (B) Every manifest datom traces to a user response (:policy/source-response ref). (C) User review step shows manifest before commit. (D) Uncertainty markers on tentative answers (confidence < 1.0). (E) braid init --manifest ddis.edn produces same store as current braid init. (F) Generated manifest passes validate_policy(). (G) The conversation observations appear in braid seed output for next session. DEPENDS-ON: POLICY-2 (t-5357604e), POLICY-5 (t-c2bb5b31). FILE: crates/braid/src/commands/init.rs" :op :assert}
